node.text:
Thank you to all the lovely humans who participated in this video - you are wonderful and your support means the world.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m really proud of this partnership with @MQmentalhealth and I hope in a small way this gives you an excuse to open up new conversations! ⁣⁣#findthelight 
⁣⁣
Sunglasses are back in stock and available now, exclusively from @baxterandbonny⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For competition terms go to: www.gemmastyles.com/ftlterms

node.text:
Scrubbed up for the @britishpodcastawards over the weekend! 🎧 Thanks so much to everyone who voted @goodinfluencegs into the Listeners’ Choice Top 10 — especially for a podcast less than a year old... me: THRILLED 🥲⁣
⁣
I was honoured to present the award for Best Wellbeing Podcast to @podcastpenny for @discoveringdementia ⭐️ ⁣
⁣
Can’t believe we’re 2/3 of the way through Season 2 of the podcast now! If you missed it, this week’s episode features @therealbenhurst on toxic masculinity and coming up next week: confidence with @calliethorpe! ⁣
⁣
📸 @milliewebber

node.text:
A self-explanatory title 💚 Last month I asked you if anyone would like to communicate their thoughts and feelings on mental illnesses that typically have less representation. The above slides are short quotes from some of the messages that you sent me — you can find them in their entirety on my website (gemmastyles.com) and if you care about increasing our levels of awareness and understanding for various mental health conditions I’d really encourage you to have a read.⁣
⁣
For my fellow sufferers of depression and anxiety: in no way do I mean that our conditions aren’t difficult and complex to deal with — there is so so much to be done in creating true understanding and treatment for these debilitating illnesses. We pass the mic to our friends who deal with our, and other illnesses, without the benefit of the awareness we already have. Love ya.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'MENTAL HEALTH AWARENESS VOICES OUTSIDE OF ANXIETY AND DEPRESSION'.

Photo by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"When I first spoke to my family about seeking help, someone very close to me said 'Nina you can't have OCD, have you seen the state of your bedroom? as ifthe clothes on the floor and the make up brushes spewed across my desk countered my intrusive and debilitating thoughts." NINA, ON OBSESSIVE COMPULSIVE DISORDER'.

Photo by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"Anorexia is a mental disorder not a body one but it is percived through a prism of one's one weight." ANONYMOUS, ON ATYPICAL ANOREXIA'.

Photo by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"Not everyone will understand, and not everyone has to, but that is one thing in my past that Iregret the most- letting bipolar disorder get in between me and others close to me." IZZY, ON BIPOLAR DISORDER II'.

Photo by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"A lot of people don't get that we know that our fear of illnesses is unreasonable. We know that there is a low chance that we're actually sick." LINN, ON HYPOCHONDRIA'.

Photo by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"Body dysmorphia and eating disorders walk hand in hand. recall looking in the mirror and feeling like my body had been the same throughout my whole battle. As for my peers, they could see my mental and physical health drastically changing." HALEY, ON BULIMIA AND BODY DYSMORPHIA'.

Photo shared by Gemma Styles on June 15, 2021 tagging @rethinkmentalillness, @mindcharity, and @mqmentalhealth. May be an image of text that says 'A friendly reminder: These are individual thoughts and experiences and will never be representative of every single person with that illness. For the full stories as well as others, visit gemmastyles.com IF YOU'D LIKE MORE INFORMATION OR SUPPORT: MQ MENTAL HEALTH RESEARCH MIND RETHINK MENTAL ILLNESS'.
